M = size(X,DIM) returns the length of the dimension specified
    by the scalar DIM.  For example, size(X,1) returns the number
    of rows. If DIM > NDIMS(X), M will be 1.
 % size扩展用法
 
 
 >> A = [1 2 3; 4 5 6];
>> A(:,1)

ans =

     1
     4

>> A(:,2)

ans =

     2
     5

>> A(:,3)

ans =

     3
     6

>> A(1,:)

ans =

     1     2     3

>> A(2,:)

ans =

     4     5     6

>> 
>> A(2,2)

ans =

     5

>> A(2,3)

ans =

     6
% ：表示所有
